-- FACTBOX: Nasdaq Composite posts worst year ever in 2008
-- 
-- Wed Dec 31, 2008 4:38pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/12/31/us-usa-stocks-nasdaq-ranking-factbox-idUSTRE4BU4MP20081231

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - The Nasdaq Composite  .IXIC  plummeted 40.5 percent in 2008, marking the worst year in its history. 

 Below is a list of the ten worst years for the index by percentage changes. Year Pct Change 2008 -40.5 2000 -39.3 1974 -31.5 2002 -21.1 1973 -17.8 2001 -11.2 1990 -5.3 1984 -3.2 1987 -3.2 1981 +1.4 Source: NASDAQ Market Intelligence Desk (Reporting by  Rodrigo Campos , Editing by Chizu Nomiyama)